4 Usage
═══════

  Please type `M-x apdl-mode' and check out the menu bar's `ANSYS' entry
  for its possibilities and select the entry `Describe APDL-Mode' or
  type "C-h m" (i. e. the <CTRL> key together with the <h> key and
  subsequently the <m> key), which will display the apdl-mode help which
  is your `online' guide for its usage, and key-bindings.

  I suggest you have a look into the introductory tutorial
  [A-M_introductory_tutorial.org].


[A-M_introductory_tutorial.org] <file:doc/A-M_introductory_tutorial.org>


5 Configuration and Customisation
═════════════════════════════════

