8.2 APDL Editor Resources
─────────────────────────

  • A free Windows [APDL editor], site not maintained since 2011
  • A commercial competitor of apdl-mode: The [Pedal] script editor for
    Windows, project disbandened in 2015.
  • Simple APDL syntax highlighting addons are available for various
    editors, gvim, nedit, … just to name a few, please have a look at
    [ANSYS.net].

  • [Stackexchange], the question and answer site.
  • [EmacsWiki], an encyclopedia for GNU-Emacs


[APDL editor] <http://apdl.de>

[Pedal] <http://www.padtinc.com/pedal>

[ANSYS.net] <http://ansys.net>

[Stackexchange] <http://emacs.stackexchange.com>

[EmacsWiki] <http://www.emacswiki.org>


8.3 ANSYS and APDL Resources
────────────────────────────

  • ANSYS manuals in the first place
  • The [ANSYS homepage] with their ANSYS Portal and Learning Hub
  • Xansys, an [ANSYS online community] (forum registration is
    necessary)
  • A general ANSYS repository [ANSYS.net]
  • [AUC], the ANSYS User Club eV in Germany

